The Torch burned for the second time in Dubai
In Dubai, one of the world's largest residential skyscrapers went up in flames on Friday. Firefighters had to evacuate all residents of the 337-meter-high and 79-storey building.
This is the second fire in the last two years at this high-rise building, which is aptly named The Torch.
All occupants of the building were evacuated and there were no injuries. The cause of the fire is unknown.
"We were asleep and we were woken up by an alarm. We heard screaming.
It took us ten minutes to run down from the 50th floor," Geroge, a skyscraper resident, told Reuters.
Dubai Civil Defence said firefighters managed to bring the fire under control around four a.m. (0:00 GMT) and continued to cool the building.
