The results of an investigation launched by Torch skyscraper management after a fire in 2015 showed that the most damaged were the cladding and external panels used for decoration or insulation.
British police said the insulation and cladding system at London's Grenfell Tower may have contributed to the rapid spread of the blaze in the June fire that killed nearly 80 people.
