The pain was indescribable.
The clothes fell apart on me like nothing and I just felt an incredible pain on my skin," Andreas said.
His family rushed him to the hospital, but there his loved ones learned terrible news - according to doctors, he had no chance of surviving.
For several weeks after the incident, doctors were constantly worried that their patient would succumb to an infection that threatened to penetrate his wounds.
His injury was very serious.
Ninety percent of the face was affected, which doctors tried to put together using skin from other parts of the patient's body.
A big complication for Christopheros was the loss of his eyelids.
It's probably the most torturous thing I've experienced.
