Four years ago, 10,000 Czech citizens voted for deputies abroad.
"Since the last amendment to the decree in 2013, there have been some changes that need to be taken into account in these lists," the ministry explains its approach.
"In some countries, new embassies have been created, some offices have been closed, or the level of representation has changed," the material says.
The decree contains two annexes, the first of which lists the embassies to which paper ballot papers are supplied.
