Eight years after its founding, Riodoce won the prestigious Maria Moors Cabot Award for its coverage of Latin America.
That same year, Valdez won the International Press Freedom Award of the Committee to Protect Journalists for his brave reporting on Mexico's drug trafficking.
Valdez openly admitted that he was afraid.
"I feared for my life," he said when accepting the award.
Drug trafficking in Sinaloae is a "way of life," Valdez said in an interview with Rompeviento TV in October last year.
"You have to take on the role of a journalist - or play stupid.
