The landscape is constantly changing.
No mobile phones are allowed in the room where Riodoca staff meet; A few days ago, spyware was discovered that governments bought to monitor Mexican journalists and activists.
Outside the building, two policemen find relief from the forty-degree heat in the shade of a nearby tree.
