One journalist read from the public record that the restaurant was registered under a name associated with a certain politician who is a member of the Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI), which has controlled all levels of the political scene for almost the last century.
Several PRI governors have recently been indicted for high-level corruption.
Villarreal asked journalists to write about earlier incidents that occurred at the restaurant, including one in which one of Joaquín "El Chapo" Guzmán's sons escaped an army riot squad.
Just a month ago, readers would have read about this topic in Valdez's column, which was the best source of information on kidnappings.
